          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The decline in the school's administration over the past few years, under the current principal and coordinators, has been evident and concerning. There's a palpable deterioration in the professionalism and conduct of the coordinators, who seem more focused on pleasing each other than addressing legitimate concerns from parents. This lax attitude has directly impacted the learning environment, with instances of unprofessional behavior towards students, including my own two children. Complaints and grievances are routinely ignored, creating an environment where accountability is sorely lacking. It's a stark departure from the exemplary leadership of Mrs. Nirmal, whose tenure as principal was marked by efficiency and effectiveness. Moreover, the alarming revelation that many teachers responsible for grades 8-12 lack proper qualifications such as a B.Ed and sufficient experience is deeply troubling. As someone who has previously recommended this institution to others, I now find myself hesitant to do so, given the evident decline in standards and professionalism. There's an urgent need for comprehensive reforms to restore the school's reputation and ensure a conducive learning environment for all students.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
